      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatographic-peak-shape-comparison/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The alignment process has also seen substantial improvements with the introduction of new algorithms and the option to base it on a subset of the data set or an external reference data set. The gap-filling step, designed to recover missing values for low-abundance features, has been improved by employing a more accurate estimation of the ions' expected m/z\u2013retention time region.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses retention-time alignment and m/z-retention time region estimation, but does not explicitly address isotopologue/adduct variant discrimination via peak morphology comparison. The claim's specific focus on distinguishing isotopologues/adducts is not directly supported.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatographic-peak-shape-comparison",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "identifies subtle retention-time shifts and peak morphology differences that distinguish features of distinct compounds from genuine isotopologue or adduct variants",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:29:10.892330+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/chromatographic-peak-shape-comparison/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Each major preprocessing step, such as peak detection, retention time alignment, and chromatographic peak grouping, is now handled by a dedicated function, with multiple algorithms available for each step. These algorithms are configured via dedicated parameter classes",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms xcms has parameter classes for preprocessing steps including peak grouping, and discusses EIC visualization capabilities. However, the paper does not explicitly name 'groupFeatures()' function or 'EicSimilarityParam' by name in the provided passages. The functional capability (EIC-based feature grouping via parameter classes) is present, but the specific function and parameter class names are not verbatim-confirmed in these passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "chromatographic-peak-shape-comparison",
