      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Users can test and fine-tune settings for each preprocessing step, leading to more informed and justifiable parameter choices. Tailored plotting functions have been developed for different stages of the analysis, whether working with the full, raw MS data or examining results at various preprocessing steps. Specifically, users can generate base peak chromatograms (BPCs) from raw data, EICs with highlighted chromatographic peaks during peak detection, and density plots for feature grouping, allowing for visual insights throughout the workflow",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses EIC visualization and feature grouping capabilities in xcms, but does not explicitly name 'EicSimilarityParam' class or describe EIC peak-shape correlation as a refinement method. The paper mentions 'parameter classes' as a general design pattern and discusses feature grouping, but the specific EicSimilarityParam functionality for EIC-based sub-grouping refinement is not verbatim present. The functional concept (EIC visualization for feature refinement) is present but the specific parameter class name and its use for peak-shape correlation-based subdivision is not confirmed.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
