    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/eic-similarity-correlation-analysis/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The alignment process has also seen substantial improvements with the introduction of new algorithms and the option to base it on a subset of the data set or an external reference data set. The gap-filling step, designed to recover missing values for low-abundance features, has been improved by employing a more accurate estimation of the ions' expected m/z\u2013retention time region. Lastly, several methods for quality control of features have been developed, adhering to widely accepted standards in metabolomics.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses retention-time alignment and feature grouping improvements, but does not explicitly describe a workflow where EIC-similarity refinement is applied after abundance-correlation-based grouping. The paper mentions alignment and grouping but does not confirm the specific sequential workflow (abundance-correlation \u2192 EIC-similarity refinement) claimed in the card.",
