    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-abundance-correlation-analysis/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "xcms has continuously evolved to meet the needs of scientists and data analysts, with several key implementations introduced to enhance its functionality. Central to these updates is the introduction of parameter classes, which form the foundation of a modular and flexible programming interface. Each major preprocessing step, such as peak detection, retention time alignment, and chromatographic peak grouping, is now handled by a dedicated function, with multiple algorithms available for each step.",
      "asbval:note": "xcms is confirmed as the preprocessing and grouping tool. The paper explicitly mentions integration with MsFeatures for feature grouping (passage 5): 'The MsFeatures package adds yet another layer of versatility in postanalysis by grouping LC-MS features that represent the signal of ions and isotopes of the same compound.'",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
