    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/feature-group-refinement-multicriteria/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The alignment process has also seen substantial improvements with the introduction of new algorithms and the option to base it on a subset of the data set or an external reference data set. The gap-filling step, designed to recover missing values for low-abundance features, has been improved by employing a more accurate estimation of the ions' expected m/z\u2013retention time region.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses retention time alignment and gap-filling improvements but does not explicitly mention a \u00b1120 s window parameter or describe a workflow of iterative refinement after initial grouping. The concept of retention-time-based grouping is present but the specific workflow and parameter are not.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "feature-group-refinement-multicriteria",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill after initial retention-time-based feature grouping (e.g., \u00b1120 s window) when you need to separate co-eluting features that are chemically distinct.",
