    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/lc-ms-feature-grouping-and-compounding/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Preprocessing is the crucial first step in analyzing untargeted liquid chromatography\u2013mass spectrometry (LC-MS)... It involves quantifying ion signals in a sample, correcting potential retention time drifts within and across analytical runs, and grouping signals from the same ion species across all samples in an experiment.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes the workflow of peak detection followed by grouping signals from the same ion species, which aligns with the scope description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "lc-ms-feature-grouping-and-compounding",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "After chromatographic peak detection on preprocessed LC-MS data, when you have hundreds or thousands of individual m/z \u00d7 retention-time peaks and need to associate them into biologically meaningful feature groups.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:30:59.240960+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/lc-ms-feature-grouping-and-compounding/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "peak quality metrics, such as those presented in Kumler et al., can be calculated either during or after peak detection, allowing users to filter the data and retain only high-confidence signals.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper mentions quality metrics and filtering for high-confidence signals, but does not explicitly mention abundance correlation thresholds (\u22650.7) or pairwise correlation validation as a specific grouping quality check.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "lc-ms-feature-grouping-and-compounding",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "validating grouping quality by examining pairwise abundance correlations (e.g., checking whether features within a group truly co-vary across samples with correlation \u2265 0.7)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:30:59.240960+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-chromatogram-alignment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The alignment process has also seen substantial improvements with the introduction of new algorithms and the option to base it on a subset of the data set or an external reference data set. The gap-filling step, designed to recover missing values for low-abundance features, has been improved by employing a more accurate estimation of the ions' expected m/z\u2013retention time region.",
      "asbval:note": "Core alignment and feature grouping functionality confirmed; m/z and retention time matching is central to xcms preprocessing workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-chromatogram-alignment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Align extracted ion chromatograms (EICs) across multiple LC-MS samples to enable feature correspondence and abundance quantification by matching m/z and retention time coordinates, producing a unified feature matrix",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:12.964823+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-chromatogram-alignment/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Each major preprocessing step, such as peak detection, retention time alignment, and chromatographic peak grouping, is now handled by a dedicated function, with multiple algorithms available for each step. These algorithms are configured via dedicated parameter classes, allowing users to easily define and customize settings based on the specific requirements of their experiment.",
      "asbval:note": "Parameter classes and modular approach confirmed; gap-filling explicitly mentioned in passage 4.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-chromatogram-alignment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms with groupFeatures() method, SimilarRtimeParam, AbundanceSimilarityParam, EicSimilarityParam, and gap-filling functionality",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
