    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-m-z-accuracy-assessment/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper focuses on LC-MS/MS preprocessing (peak detection, retention time alignment, feature grouping) in xcms. No mention of FTICR-MS, direct injection MS, m/z calibration assessment, calibrant mass comparison, or m/z bias quantification. The paper discusses xcms as a preprocessing tool for LC-MS data, not as a tool for m/z accuracy assessment or calibration validation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-m-z-accuracy-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Quantify and visualize m/z measurement accuracy before and after calibration in FTICR-MS or other high-resolution direct injection MS data by comparing observed m/z values against expected calibrant masses.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:45.870219+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-m-z-accuracy-assessment/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "xcms has continuously evolved to meet the needs of scientists and data analysts, with several key implementations introduced to enhance its functionality. Central to these updates is the introduction of parameter classes, which form the foundation of a modular and flexible programming interface. Each major preprocessing step, such as peak detection, retention time alignment, and chromatographic peak grouping, is now handled by a dedicated function, with multiple algorithms available for each step. These algorithms are configured via dedicated parameter classes",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms xcms supports mzML files, peak detection via dedicated functions (including chromatographic peak detection), and parameter classes for configuration. However, no mention of CalibrantMassParam or mass calibration functionality in xcms. The paper discusses peak detection, retention time alignment, and feature grouping, but does not address m/z calibration or calibrant-based mass correction as a preprocessing step in xcms.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-m-z-accuracy-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms \u2014 Load mzML files, detect chromatographic peaks with findChromPeaks(), apply mass calibration with CalibrantMassParam, and retrieve calibrated m/z values",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:45.870219+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrometry-m-z-accuracy-assessment/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The core data structures of xcms were completely rewritten to gain full support for LC-MS/MS data, as demonstrated in the Supporting File S2 and the GNPS molecular networking case study. These new data structures rely on the established MS data infrastructures of MSnbase and packages from the RforMassSpectrometry initiative, in particular, the Spectra and Chromatograms R packages.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Spectra package integrates with xcms for data structure support and MS data handling. Spectra is part of the RforMassSpectrometry initiative and provides infrastructure for xcms version 4+.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "mass-spectrometry-m-z-accuracy-assessment",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Spectra \u2014 Alternative container for spectral data that integrates with xcms version 4 for flexible m/z and intensity access",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:45.870219+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-data-structure-handling/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The core data structures of xcms were completely rewritten to gain full support for LC-MS/MS data... These new data structures rely on the established MS data infrastructures of MSnbase and packages from the RforMassSpectrometry initiative, in particular, the Spectra and Chromatograms R packages... The MsExperiment package provides a structured and user-oriented infrastructure that organizes experimental metadata and data files in a way that is directly compatible with xcms... MS/MS spectra extracted from xcms objects can be used with the MetaboAnnotation package for matching against reference fragment spectra.",
      "asbval:note": "Core claim fully supported: paper explicitly describes XcmsExperiment, MsExperiment, and Spectra as modern container objects for LC-MS data, and discusses integration with downstream annotation and spectral matching.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolomics-data-structure-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Load, validate, and manipulate LC-MS metabolomics data using modern Bioconductor container objects (XcmsExperiment, MsExperiment, Spectra) to enable seamless integration with downstream feature grouping, annotation, and spectral matching workflows.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:31:56.923680+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-data-structure-handling/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "xcms has continuously evolved to meet the needs of scientists and data analysts... Each major preprocessing step, such as peak detection, retention time alignment, and chromatographic peak grouping, is now handled by a dedicated function... The core data structures of xcms were completely rewritten to gain full support for LC-MS/MS data",
      "asbval:note": "xcms is confirmed as the primary tool for LC-MS preprocessing and data container management. Specific accessor methods (chromPeaks, featureValues, chromPeakSpectra) are not explicitly named in passages, but the functional role is clearly supported.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolomics-data-structure-handling",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms \u2014 Provides XcmsExperiment/xcmsSet container and accessor methods (chromPeaks, featureValues, chromPeakSpectra) for loading and validating preprocessed LC-MS data",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
