    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-abundance-correlation-visualization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "peak quality metrics, such as those presented in Kumler et al., can be calculated either during or after peak detection, allowing users to filter the data and retain only high-confidence signals... The alignment process has also seen substantial improvements with the introduction of new algorithms and the option to base it on a subset of the data set or an external reference data set. The gap-filling step, designed to recover missing values for low-abundance features, has been improved by employing a more accurate estimation of the ions' expected m/z\u2013retention time region.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses retention-time alignment, gap-filling, and feature grouping, but does not explicitly discuss abundance-correlation-based visualization or AbundanceSimilarityParam. The paper mentions feature grouping and quality metrics but does not detail abundance correlation visualization as a specific workflow step.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "retention-time-abundance-correlation-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Visualize pairwise abundance correlations across samples within retention-time-based feature groups after abundance-similarity refinement, to assess which co-eluting features exhibit correlated ion abundance patterns and therefore likely derive from the same chemical compound.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:53.960838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/retention-time-abundance-correlation-visualization/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Each major preprocessing step, such as peak detection, retention time alignment, and chromatographic peak grouping, is now handled by a dedicated function, with multiple algorithms available for each step. These algorithms are configured via dedicated parameter classes, allowing users to easily define and customize settings based on the specific requirements of their experiment.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms xcms has parameter classes and grouping functions, but does not explicitly name 'groupFeatures()' function or 'AbundanceSimilarityParam' class. The paper discusses parameter classes for peak detection, alignment, and grouping generically but does not detail abundance-similarity-specific parameters.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "retention-time-abundance-correlation-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms provides groupFeatures() function and AbundanceSimilarityParam class to perform abundance-correlation-based feature refinement on retention-time groups; also handles log2 transformation and gap-filling.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:32:53.960838+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
