    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "xcms has since been cited over 3800 times and was downloaded over 150,000 times by distinct IP addresses since the introduction of download statistics in Bioconductor in 2009. Over the two decades since its initial release, xcms has undergone significant transformations to address the aforementioned challenges while maintaining its core principles of flexibility, external collaboration, and open-source innovation.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms xcms is used for LC-MS/MS data preprocessing and import; XCMSnExp objects are the standard xcms result container for this purpose, consistent with paper's discussion of xcms data structures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Load LC-MS/MS raw data files (mzML, NetCDF, or mzXML) into xcms XCMSnExp objects",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For example, peak detection is now coupled with peak filtering and refinement, addressing artifacts that can arise in the initial steps by postprocessing detected chromatographic peaks and removing or merging them if necessary. Additionally, peak quality metrics, such as those presented in Kumler et al., can be calculated either during or after peak detection, allowing users to filter the data and retain only high-confidence signals. These improved filtering approaches help minimize the inclusion of likely false-positive peaks, a common issue in earlier studies. \u2212 The alignment process has also seen substantial improvements with the introduction of new algorithms and the option to base it on a subset of the data set or an external reference data set. The gap-filling step, designed to recover missing values for low-abundance features, has been improved by employing a more accurate estimation of the ions' expected m/z\u2013retention time region.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms peak detection and retention time alignment/filtering. Mass calibration (edgeshift method) is mentioned in the card but not explicitly found in passages; paper discusses m/z-retention time region estimation but does not name 'edgeshift' or explicit mass calibration as a preprocessing step in the provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "apply initial preprocessing including chromatographic peak detection, mass calibration, and retention time filtering",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The core data structures of xcms were completely rewritten to gain full support for LC-MS/MS data, as demonstrated in the Supporting File S2 and the GNPS molecular networking case study. These new data structures rely on the established MS data infrastructures of MSnbase and packages from the RforMassSpectrometry initiative, \u2212 in particular, the Spectra and Chromatograms R packages.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms xcms converts raw data into standardized R objects (via MSnbase, Spectra, Chromatograms) for downstream analysis.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "converting instrument output into a standardized R object amenable to downstream feature detection and grouping",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Since its introduction in 2005, the xcms R package has become one of the most widely used tools for LC-MS data preprocessing. Preprocessing is the crucial first step in analyzing untargeted liquid chromatography\u2013mass spectrometry (LC-MS) or gas chromatography\u2013mass spectrometry (GC-MS) data. It involves quantifying ion signals in a sample, correcting potential retention time drifts within and across analytical runs, and grouping signals from the same ion species across all samples in an experiment.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms xcms handles LC-MS data import, peak detection, and retention time correction. However, 'edgeshift method' for mass calibration is not mentioned in the provided passages; paper discusses m/z-retention time region estimation but does not name this specific calibration method.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms \u2014 Core R package for LC-MS data import, chromatographic peak detection, mass calibration (edgeshift method), and retention time filtering; handles mzML/NetCDF file I/O and produces XCMSnExp result objects",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "These new data structures rely on the established MS data infrastructures of MSnbase and packages from the RforMassSpectrometry initiative, \u2212 in particular, the Spectra and Chromatograms R packages.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly confirms MSnbase provides data structures used by xcms.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MSnbase \u2014 Provides underlying MS data structures and spectra handling used by xcms",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "These new data structures rely on the established MS data infrastructures of MSnbase and packages from the RforMassSpectrometry initiative, \u2212 in particular, the Spectra and Chromatograms R packages. Apart from a tighter integration with other R packages that will be discussed in the following section, this redesign significantly enhances xcms' ability to handle, subset, and filter data while also ensuring compatibility with emerging data formats.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Spectra is part of xcms version 4+ data structures for spectrum representation and preprocessing.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Spectra \u2014 New data container supported by xcms version 4+ for flexible spectrum representation and preprocessing",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MsExperiment package provides a structured and user-oriented infrastructure that organizes experimental metadata and data files in a way that is directly compatible with xcms.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MsExperiment is compatible with xcms for organizing multi-sample experiments; consistent with card's claim about xcms version 4+ support.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MsExperiment \u2014 Container for multi-sample MS experiments; xcms version 4+ performs preprocessing on MsExperiment objects",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "BiocParallel is not mentioned in the provided passages. Paper discusses performance improvements and scalability but does not explicitly name BiocParallel as the tool enabling parallel processing.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": null,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "BiocParallel \u2014 Enables parallel processing of chromatographic peak detection across multiple files",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000302"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000341"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-data-import-preprocessing/008",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Preprocessing software must accommodate data from various column types, such as reversed-phase (RP) chromatography and hydrophilic interaction liquid chromatography (HILIC), which produce diverse metabolite separations and chromatographic peak structures. As high-resolution mass spectrometers like Quadrupole-Time-of-Flight (QTOF) and Orbitrap become increasingly common, and with growing demand for high-throughput metabolomics, data processing tools must keep pace with increasing data complexity and volume.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses xcms handling diverse data types and formats but does not explicitly list mzML, NetCDF, or mzXML by name in the provided passages. Paper mentions 'expanded support for diverse mass spectrometry (MS) data formats' but specific format names are not enumerated in the excerpts provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-data-import-preprocessing",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "mzML, NetCDF, or mzXML format file support",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:33:40.649575+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Preprocessing is the crucial first step in analyzing untargeted liquid chromatography\u2013mass spectrometry (LC-MS)... It involves quantifying ion signals in a sample, correcting potential retention time drifts within and across analytical runs, and grouping signals from the same ion species across all samples in an experiment... peak detection is now coupled with peak filtering and refinement... The alignment process has also seen substantial improvements... The gap-filling step, designed to recover missing values for low-abundance features, has been improved...",
      "asbval:note": "Core preprocessing steps (peak detection, alignment/feature correspondence, gap-filling) are explicitly described as xcms functionality.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Execute a complete LC-MS data preprocessing pipeline using xcms, encompassing chromatographic peak detection, feature correspondence, and optional gap-filling to produce a quantitative feature abundance table from raw mass spectrometry data.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "xcms has evolved far beyond its initial role as a preprocessing tool, becoming a core component of a flexible, scalable, and interoperable LC-MS/MS data analysis ecosystem... using xcms with R Markdown, or the recently introduced R interface of the Quarto system, allows one to document and describe the analysis and its results transparently.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper emphasizes xcms as a reproducible workflow tool for metabolomics.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill chains multiple xcms methods into a reproducible workflow suitable for metabolomics studies.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Each major preprocessing step, such as peak detection, retention time alignment, and chromatographic peak grouping, is now handled by a dedicated function, with multiple algorithms available for each step.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms xcms provides dedicated functions for peak detection, alignment, and grouping. Function names (findChromPeaks, groupFeatures, fillChromPeaks) are standard xcms nomenclature consistent with the paper's description of these steps.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "xcms (Core package providing findChromPeaks(), groupFeatures(), fillChromPeaks(), and feature correspondence methods)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MsFeatures package adds yet another layer of versatility in postanalysis by grouping LC-MS features that represent the signal of ions and isotopes of the same compound.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MsFeatures provides feature grouping functionality. Specific parameter class names are not mentioned in passages but are consistent with xcms/Bioconductor conventions for feature grouping.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MsFeatures (Provides general MS feature grouping functionality and parameter classes: SimilarRtimeParam, AbundanceSimilarityParam, EicSimilarityParam)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The MsExperiment package provides a structured and user-oriented infrastructure that organizes experimental metadata and data files in a way that is directly compatible with xcms.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MsExperiment's role as a container for organizing experimental data and metadata compatible with xcms.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MsExperiment (Container class for organizing raw spectra and results in version 4 xcms workflows)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The core data structures of xcms were completely rewritten to gain full support for LC-MS/MS data... These new data structures rely on the established MS data infrastructures of MSnbase and packages from the RforMassSpectrometry initiative, in particular, the Spectra and Chromatograms R packages.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Spectra as a backend infrastructure for xcms data structures in the redesigned system.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Spectra (Backend for efficient access to raw LC-MS spectra in xcms version 4)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Preprocessing software must accommodate data from various column types, such as reversed-phase (RP) chromatography and hydrophilic interaction liquid chromatography (HILIC)... As high-resolution mass spectrometers like Quadrupole-Time-of-Flight (QTOF) and Orbitrap become increasingly common...",
      "asbval:note": "Paper discusses xcms handling of diverse data formats and mass spectrometer types. Specific file formats (mzML, netCDF) are standard metabolomics formats consistent with xcms capabilities.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Input: Raw LC-MS data files (mzML, netCDF, or vendor formats)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/xcms-workflow-execution/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Nevertheless, some limitations remain. For example, while support for ion mobility data exists at the backend level, current preprocessing algorithms do not yet exploit the ion mobility dimension.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly acknowledges that ion mobility data support is limited at the preprocessing algorithm level.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c04338",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "xcms-workflow-execution",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When NOT to use: Data are from ion mobility MS or other non-traditional LC-MS acquisition modes not explicitly supported by the article's workflow.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T12:34:00.786969+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
